    "statementHTML": "<div class=\"statement-body\">\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-goal\">\n   <h2><span class=\"icon icon-goal\">&nbsp;</span><span>Goal </span></h2>\n   <span class=\"question-statement\">It's Jack's birthday! His friends bought him a cake that is <var>l</var> units long and <var>w</var> units wide. He wants to cut the cake into <var>f</var> pieces to share with all his friends. Can you help him cut it?</span>\n</div>\n<div class=\"statement-section statement-protocol\">\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-input\"><strong>line 1</strong>: <var>l</var>, the length of the cake<br><strong>line 2</strong>: <var>w</var>, the width of the cake<br><strong>line 3</strong>: <var>f</var>, the number of pieces he wants his cake cut into.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Output</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-output\">Output <var>w</var> <strong>lines</strong> each of <var>l</var> length, as follows:<br>a &quot;#&quot; for every piece of uncut unit of cake, and<br>a &quot;|&quot; for every unit of cake that he needs to cut across vertically.<br>The cake must be cut vertically, and cannot be cut horizontally.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Constraints</div>\n      <div class=\"question-statement-constraints\">1 &lt;= <var>l</var>, <var>w</var> &lt;= <const>50</const><br>1 &lt;= <var>f</var> &lt;= <const>11</const><br>Every slice of cake will always be the same size.<br>All variable <var>l</var>, <var>w</var>, and <var>f</var> will always be integers.</div>\n   </div>\n   <div class=\"blk\">\n      <div class=\"title\">Example</div>\n      <div class=\"statement-inout\">\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-in\">\n            <div class=\"title\">Input</div>\n            <pre class=\"question-statement-example-in\">7\n3\n2</pre>\n         </div>\n         <div class=\"statement-inout-out\">\n     